00:28:32,760 --> 00:28:34,040
Ling, my ass.

517
00:30:18,360 --> 00:30:22,120
It's debilitating to know that after years
of pretending you do,

518
00:30:22,200 --> 00:30:24,920
you actually don't have
the killer instinct.

519
00:30:25,720 --> 00:30:28,480
I wanted to rip Phil's throat out last night,
but I couldn't.

520
00:30:29,480 --> 00:30:31,400
Hey, can you help me out?

521
00:30:36,440 --> 00:30:38,760
My brother Anthony
had the killer instinct.

522
00:30:38,840 --> 00:30:40,840
Anthony went after
everything he ever wanted.

523
00:30:40,920 --> 00:30:42,200
Anthony was like my father.

524
00:30:42,280 --> 00:30:44,760
He was driven and had purpose.

525
00:30:48,920 --> 00:30:51,560
When you want something in life,
you have to fight for it.

526
00:30:55,560 --> 00:30:58,480
Stay with it.
See it through.

527
00:30:58,560 --> 00:31:01,960
You have to be willing
to go the distance in life.

528
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:05,320
I wasn't willing to fight
the fight for Leah.

529
00:31:06,040 --> 00:31:08,160
And I couldn't go
the distance with Nina.

530
00:31:31,960 --> 00:31:34,120
What I think you are starting to see,

531
00:31:34,200 --> 00:31:35,200
if you're doing the work,

532
00:31:35,240 --> 00:31:36,320
if you're staying with the course,

533
00:31:36,400 --> 00:31:39,880
is that being honest every day,

534
00:31:39,960 --> 00:31:42,720
knowing what you think,
knowing what you feel,

535
00:31:42,760 --> 00:31:45,520
is getting very revealing.

536
00:31:45,600 --> 00:31:48,640
Doors are being opened.

537
00:31:48,720 --> 00:31:51,840
Boxes that have not been rummaged in
for quite some time

538
00:31:51,920 --> 00:31:53,040
are being looked through.

539
00:31:53,120 --> 00:31:58,080
Later, as we wind the course down
and I read your Journals,

540
00:31:58,160 --> 00:31:59,840
I should know you intimately,

541
00:31:59,920 --> 00:32:02,400
perhaps better than
anyone else knows you,

542
00:32:02,480 --> 00:32:03,640
except, of course, yourself.

543
00:32:03,720 --> 00:32:05,120
- Excuse me.
- Sir.

544
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:07,080
What do you mean,
read our Journals?

545
00:32:07,120 --> 00:32:09,360
I don't think that's
gonna work for me.

546
00:32:09,440 --> 00:32:11,400
I'm a very private person.

547
00:32:11,480 --> 00:32:13,520
Okay. But you may as well leave now,

548
00:32:13,600 --> 00:32:17,520
because there is really
no point in your staying.

549
00:32:17,600 --> 00:32:19,080
Well, it's not that.
I'm Just not that comfortable.

550
00:32:19,160 --> 00:32:22,960
I'm not interested
in your comfort.

551
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:25,920
I'm not an anesthetist,
I'm a doctor.

552
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:29,600
I do not get cheap thrills
reading someone's Journal.

553
00:32:29,680 --> 00:32:36,760
I am here to give you the tools
to help you to uncover...

554
00:32:39,960 --> 00:32:43,000
...discover,

555
00:32:43,720 --> 00:32:47,040
and discard...

556
00:32:47,120 --> 00:32:49,720
the crap that is
holding you back.

557
00:32:50,520 --> 00:32:51,720
And you, sir,

558
00:32:51,800 --> 00:32:54,520
definitely have crap
that is holding you back.

559
00:32:56,080 --> 00:33:00,720
"If a way to the better there be,
it exacts a full look at the worst."

560
00:33:00,760 --> 00:33:02,280
Thomas Hardy.

561
00:33:02,360 --> 00:33:03,200
Who?

562
00:33:03,280 --> 00:33:05,320
Who is Thomas Hardy?
Is that what you're asking?

563
00:33:05,400 --> 00:33:06,880
Yes, I am.

564
00:33:06,960 --> 00:33:08,960
Are you not a college man,
Mr. Giamoro?

565
00:33:09,560 --> 00:33:11,440
Community college.
Two years.

566
00:33:11,480 --> 00:33:13,960
But I believe education
can only take you so far.

567
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:15,440
Quite right.

568
00:33:15,480 --> 00:33:17,480
Absolutely true.

569
00:33:17,520 --> 00:33:19,960
But ego...

570
00:33:26,040 --> 00:33:27,920
...will not get you
the rest of the way.

571
00:33:27,960 --> 00:33:29,960
It will feed you, yes.

572
00:33:30,080 --> 00:33:32,160
It will clothe you well.

573
00:33:32,240 --> 00:33:36,920
But it will leave you cold and alone
and unknowing, I promise.

574
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:40,280
But if you would prefer to leave,
please go.

575
00:33:41,840 --> 00:33:43,960
- I don't choose to leave.
- Very well.

576
00:33:44,040 --> 00:33:45,880
So, when I ask you
to turn in your Journal

577
00:33:45,960 --> 00:33:50,080
for me and me alone
to read, Just do it.

578
00:33:50,160 --> 00:33:51,280
And remember the spelling!

579
00:33:51,320 --> 00:33:53,160
It's a thing with me.

580
00:34:12,120 --> 00:34:13,360
Hey, don't worry.

581
00:34:13,400 --> 00:34:15,600
We're gonna get this guy.

582
00:34:15,640 --> 00:34:17,760
We'll mess him up real good.

583
00:34:17,840 --> 00:34:19,280
Teach him a lesson.

584
00:34:19,960 --> 00:34:22,040
He needs one.
Playing gatekeeper.

585
00:34:22,680 --> 00:34:25,680
All these people deciding
who does and doesn't get in.

586
00:34:27,680 --> 00:34:30,040
You've been wronged,
so I'm going to fix it.

587
00:34:39,800 --> 00:34:41,040
- Hello?
- Jack.

588
00:34:41,080 --> 00:34:42,000
Hey, man, look, it's Phil.

589
00:34:42,040 --> 00:34:44,000
We need to talk.

590
00:34:44,080 --> 00:34:45,760
What do we need to
talk about, Phil?

591
00:34:45,840 --> 00:34:48,320
Come on, man.
Don't be an asshole, okay?

592
00:34:48,400 --> 00:34:52,560
I'm sorry.
I feel like shit.

593
00:34:52,600 --> 00:34:54,800
I want to see you.

594
00:34:54,840 --> 00:34:56,080
It's 8:02, Phil.

595
00:34:56,120 --> 00:34:57,640
I'm running late.

596
00:35:03,840 --> 00:35:05,360
I don't want to talk to him!

597
00:35:05,640 --> 00:35:06,600
I won't ever talk to him again!

598
00:35:06,680 --> 00:35:08,280
You sit down here.
Okay?

599
00:35:08,320 --> 00:35:10,600
Now I really do not want
to hear any more about this.

600
00:35:10,680 --> 00:35:12,320
Of all the girls in the world,

601
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:14,520
you had to steal one
from your baby brother?

602
00:35:14,600 --> 00:35:17,200
You should be ashamed!

603
00:35:17,280 --> 00:35:18,800
Anthony!

604
00:35:23,520 --> 00:35:25,720
I Just don't want to come home

605
00:35:25,800 --> 00:35:28,360
and listen to the same garbage
every night.

606
00:35:28,440 --> 00:35:30,360
I come home from work,
I got a headache.

607
00:35:30,400 --> 00:35:33,080
I've been shit on all day,
and then I have to listen

608
00:35:33,160 --> 00:35:35,160
to this crap night after night!

609
00:35:35,200 --> 00:35:36,600
I don't understand why!

610
00:35:36,640 --> 00:35:38,560
Anthony needs to do
the right thing!

611
00:35:38,640 --> 00:35:39,600
Oh, come on!

612
00:35:39,680 --> 00:35:42,560
I am taking him over to her house
to talk this out with her parents!

613
00:35:42,640 --> 00:35:44,240
Anthony,
open this door now!

614
00:35:44,320 --> 00:35:46,280
Leave the kid alone!
You're driving me nuts!

615
00:35:46,360 --> 00:35:49,120
Get down those stairs
and get out in that car right now!

616
00:35:49,920 --> 00:35:51,800
You stay out of this!

617
00:35:51,880 --> 00:35:53,200
My mother never forgave my father

618
00:35:53,280 --> 00:35:56,840
for letting the failure of his career
destroy his happiness at home.

619
00:35:58,080 --> 00:35:59,760
She never forgave him
for putting a wall up

620
00:35:59,840 --> 00:36:01,600
between himself
and his two sons.

621
00:36:01,680 --> 00:36:02,720
You only care about Jack!

622
00:36:02,800 --> 00:36:04,280
My father never forgave me

623
00:36:04,320 --> 00:36:06,680
for not being thin and focused,

624
00:36:06,720 --> 00:36:09,120
combative and determined
like Anthony.

625
00:36:09,160 --> 00:36:10,120
Between you
and your father...

626
00:36:16,720 --> 00:36:18,560
And for the rest of her life,

627
00:36:18,640 --> 00:36:23,200
he never forgave my mother
for killing Anthony.

628
00:36:33,200 --> 00:36:37,040
Why the hell should I
have to forgive Nina?

629
00:36:38,240 --> 00:36:40,240
- You've got about a hundred calls.
- David Lilly?

630
00:36:40,320 --> 00:36:42,000
No, but I did figure out
who Barbi Ling is.

631
00:36:42,080 --> 00:36:44,600
<i>She writes freelance hatchet pieces
for the L.A. Voice.</i>

632
00:36:44,680 --> 00:36:46,000
Most of them are
maJor players in town.

633
00:36:46,040 --> 00:36:47,680
She did the Sherry Lansing piece.

634
00:36:47,760 --> 00:36:49,200
- Figures.
- It gets worse.

635
00:36:49,280 --> 00:36:51,440
She's a screenwriter
and was a stand-up comic.

636
00:36:51,520 --> 00:36:53,280
You know, one of them
Comedy Store wanna-bes?

637
00:36:53,360 --> 00:36:55,280
She submitted ten scripts
within the last five years.

638
00:36:55,360 --> 00:36:56,480
We reJected them all.

639
00:36:56,560 --> 00:36:57,600
She couldn't make it in this town

640
00:36:57,680 --> 00:36:58,800
and decided to tear down
the people who did, right?

641
00:36:58,880 --> 00:36:59,840
It gets worse.

642
00:36:59,920 --> 00:37:00,920
Would you stop saying that, please?

643
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:02,520
You sound like a bit player
on a Dick Wolf show.

644
00:37:02,600 --> 00:37:04,720
<i>She sold a full profile to the L.A. Voice.</i>

645
00:37:04,760 --> 00:37:06,080
The one last week was
Just a teaser.

646
00:37:06,160 --> 00:37:07,560
She's doing a whole thing
on you, Jack...

647
00:37:07,640 --> 00:37:09,200
the evolution of the agency,
the stealing of clients.

648
00:37:09,240 --> 00:37:11,120
Please tell me that's not true.

649
00:37:11,160 --> 00:37:12,400
- I can't.
- Jack.

650
00:37:12,480 --> 00:37:13,520
We need you in your office.

651
00:37:13,600 --> 00:37:15,280
Right now.

652
00:37:15,320 --> 00:37:18,000
Jack, it's important.

653
00:37:18,040 --> 00:37:18,880
Phil called.

654
00:37:18,960 --> 00:37:20,120
He wants to sit down with you

655
00:37:20,200 --> 00:37:21,320
or he's threatened
to leave the agency.

656
00:37:21,400 --> 00:37:22,360
You need to have lunch with him.

657
00:37:22,440 --> 00:37:23,880
I'm not sitting down with Phil.

658
00:37:23,960 --> 00:37:25,120
Nina called me, too.

659
00:37:25,200 --> 00:37:26,760
She's destroyed.
You need to see her.

660
00:37:26,840 --> 00:37:27,920
I'm worried about her.

661
00:37:27,960 --> 00:37:29,440
Then you see her.

662
00:37:30,560 --> 00:37:33,040
Hey, get this Ling
on the phone, will ya?

663
00:37:33,120 --> 00:37:34,160
Jack, you need to do something.

664
00:37:34,240 --> 00:37:35,920
He will leave the agency.

665
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:39,160
Jack, here's how bad
I want you to have lunch with Phil.

666
00:37:39,240 --> 00:37:40,200
Are you ready?

667
00:37:40,280 --> 00:37:46,280
I will sign your cousin Andrew's no-talent,
acne-scarred daughter.

668
00:37:46,360 --> 00:37:48,080
Okay?

669
00:37:50,880 --> 00:37:52,760
- Call him.
- Jack, Barbi Ling on line 3.

670
00:37:54,120 --> 00:37:56,560
Barbi Ling, how are you?

671
00:37:56,600 --> 00:37:57,880
I'm fine, Mr. Giamoro.

672
00:37:57,920 --> 00:37:58,960
What can I do for you?

673
00:37:59,040 --> 00:38:01,400
Well, I think that you
and I should sit down

674
00:38:01,440 --> 00:38:02,400
and have a meal together.

675
00:38:02,480 --> 00:38:05,080
Why? Do I sound hungry?

676
00:38:05,120 --> 00:38:07,880
In fact, when you called,
I was having a meal.

677
00:38:07,960 --> 00:38:09,720
Well, if you're like me,

678
00:38:09,760 --> 00:38:12,600
eventually you'll have another one.

679
00:38:12,640 --> 00:38:13,640
Listen to me, Barbi.

680
00:38:13,720 --> 00:38:15,720
I promise you,
you need me close on this, okay?

681
00:38:15,800 --> 00:38:16,880
Profiles need information.

682
00:38:16,920 --> 00:38:18,480
I can get you to who
you need to get to

683
00:38:18,560 --> 00:38:20,680
so you can get
this thing done right.

684
00:38:20,760 --> 00:38:21,840
Are we done?

685
00:38:21,880 --> 00:38:24,360
Barbi, I'm being nice now.

686
00:38:24,440 --> 00:38:26,440
This is the nice Jack
that you're talking to.

687
00:38:26,520 --> 00:38:28,720
I know.
And I'm so very lucky.

688
00:38:28,800 --> 00:38:32,480
Oh, look!
My food's here.

689
00:38:34,040 --> 00:38:36,280
Fun meeting you,
nice Jack.

690
00:38:39,280 --> 00:38:41,200
I'm not good with the word "no."

691
00:38:41,280 --> 00:38:43,040
I never have been.

692
00:38:44,600 --> 00:38:48,280
I worked at the world-famous
Cameron Merrick Agency.

693
00:38:48,320 --> 00:38:51,040
Morty, Arlene and I
all started in the mailroom together.

694
00:38:51,120 --> 00:38:52,360
We were young and hungry

695
00:38:52,440 --> 00:38:54,680
and had the power
of determination.

696
00:38:55,520 --> 00:38:59,320
Once I found the business,
I knew I was gonna succeed.

697
00:38:59,360 --> 00:39:01,880
I saw myself
succeeding so clearly

698
00:39:01,960 --> 00:39:03,800
that it became
a moment in time

699
00:39:03,840 --> 00:39:06,840
that I had but simply
to wait and prepare for.

700
00:39:06,920 --> 00:39:10,120
Like a bus scheduled into the station
at a preordained moment,

701
00:39:10,200 --> 00:39:14,280
I moved forward with confidence
that my day would surely arrive.

702
00:39:14,360 --> 00:39:16,920
And when the time came
to make a play,

703
00:39:16,960 --> 00:39:18,400
I made a play.

704
00:39:19,040 --> 00:39:22,040
As our bosses before us had done,
we formed a new group,

705
00:39:22,160 --> 00:39:24,320
took most of our clients,
and left the agency.

706
00:39:24,960 --> 00:39:27,240
But first we copied all their secrets

707
00:39:27,320 --> 00:39:30,200
so we'd have something to blackmail them with
if they ever came after us.

708
00:39:31,200 --> 00:39:35,000
It was ruthless and bold,
a mailroom coup,

709
00:39:35,040 --> 00:39:37,440
a time-honored
show business tradition.

710
00:39:48,800 --> 00:39:51,200
Change is coming around again now.

711
00:39:52,000 --> 00:39:53,440
I can feel it.

712
00:40:16,040 --> 00:40:17,720
Dad?

713
00:40:28,280 --> 00:40:29,640
Dad?

714
00:41:35,320 --> 00:41:36,800
Goddamn it!

715
00:42:05,640 --> 00:42:06,760
Hi.

716
00:42:09,960 --> 00:42:11,360
Is he gonna be okay?

717
00:42:12,520 --> 00:42:14,680
He's banged up.

718
00:42:14,760 --> 00:42:16,840
He's got a couple
fractured ribs.

719
00:42:16,880 --> 00:42:19,800
Pretty bad cut
on his back.

720
00:42:19,880 --> 00:42:20,520
He's gonna
need to see a dentist.

721
00:42:20,600 --> 00:42:23,440
His teeth are pretty bad.

722
00:42:24,560 --> 00:42:26,040
It's not a problem, Jack.

723
00:42:26,600 --> 00:42:28,600
I've got the best guy
in Beverly Hills.

724
00:42:28,680 --> 00:42:31,720
And Jack, the best thing about it is,
you won't feel a thing.

725
00:42:31,760 --> 00:42:33,880
This guy will have you
on so much dope.

726
00:42:33,960 --> 00:42:35,840
You're gonna love this guy.

727
00:42:51,920 --> 00:42:52,840
Wait a minute!

728
00:42:52,920 --> 00:42:55,200
He's not a dentist!
He's a comedy writer!

729
00:42:55,280 --> 00:42:57,040
This guy's a comedy writer!

730
00:42:57,120 --> 00:42:59,080
Okay, we better up that dosage, please.
Thank you.

731
00:43:13,400 --> 00:43:17,040
Who let...
Who let the whore in?

732
00:43:17,080 --> 00:43:18,800
You're a whore!

733
00:43:18,880 --> 00:43:21,360
She broke the bonds
of our matrimony!

734
00:43:21,400 --> 00:43:23,280
You screwed my biggest client!

735
00:43:23,320 --> 00:43:25,600
Why couldn't you screw Garry Marshall?
He's about to retire!

736
00:43:25,680 --> 00:43:28,160
You had to screw
a working client!

737
00:43:28,240 --> 00:43:29,360
That's good!

738
00:43:31,240 --> 00:43:32,600
I'll be in the waiting room.

739
00:44:30,320 --> 00:44:32,640
Morty, he's here!
Morty!

740
00:44:32,720 --> 00:44:34,640
Okay, good.
Did you tell Arlene?

741
00:44:34,720 --> 00:44:35,880
- Yeah, she knows.
- Okay.

742
00:44:35,960 --> 00:44:36,880
I'm here.
Where's Fineberg?

743
00:44:36,960 --> 00:44:38,160
He's on his way.

744
00:44:38,240 --> 00:44:39,840
- Okay.
- Okay.

745
00:44:39,920 --> 00:44:41,240
Nobody mentions the teeth.
Okay?

746
00:44:41,320 --> 00:44:42,200
Come on.
Come on, come on.

747
00:44:42,280 --> 00:44:44,440
Talk about his quick recovery.
Talk about how good he looks.

748
00:44:44,520 --> 00:44:45,520
- Come on.
- He likes that.

749
00:44:45,600 --> 00:44:47,040
Okay, quick! Thank you.

750
00:44:47,120 --> 00:44:48,520
Everybody upbeat? Okay.

751
00:45:06,160 --> 00:45:07,760
So, how you doing, Jack?

752
00:45:09,680 --> 00:45:10,400
How you think I'm doing?

753
00:45:11,600 --> 00:45:13,560
I look like a goddamn xylophone!

754
00:45:14,160 --> 00:45:16,120
Jack, Kevin Sands is
the best in the business.

755
00:45:16,200 --> 00:45:17,600
He does all the big names.

756
00:45:17,640 --> 00:45:19,480
You were in
so much pain and so wild.

757
00:45:19,560 --> 00:45:21,360
He did the best he could.

758
00:45:21,440 --> 00:45:24,480
I look like Tom Cruise's retarded cousin.

759
00:45:26,320 --> 00:45:27,280
Jack, what did the cops say?

760
00:45:27,360 --> 00:45:29,160
Did they find anything?

761
00:45:29,200 --> 00:45:32,360
No. Guy got away.

762
00:45:32,400 --> 00:45:33,920
They have no idea who he was.

763
00:45:34,000 --> 00:45:36,840
Well, the important thing
is that you're back, right?

764
00:45:36,880 --> 00:45:39,360
Yep, I'm back!

765
00:45:42,160 --> 00:45:44,400
All right, I'll see you guys.

766
00:48:00,480 --> 00:48:02,160
Maria?

767
00:48:06,160 --> 00:48:08,320
Have you seen my Journal?

768
00:48:12,120 --> 00:48:13,640
Maria!

769
00:48:24,120 --> 00:48:26,160
My home was broken into
and it was stolen.

770
00:48:26,200 --> 00:48:27,840
I haven't had an entry
in three weeks.

771
00:48:27,920 --> 00:48:29,320
So, what's your plan?

772
00:48:31,080 --> 00:48:32,360
