going ahead with the story.

966
00:59:31,560 --> 00:59:33,240
Here's a little tip.

967
00:59:33,320 --> 00:59:36,960
Tearing down other people
who worked hard to get where they are

968
00:59:37,040 --> 00:59:39,640
is not a way to
advance your career.

969
00:59:41,240 --> 00:59:42,240
My Journal, please.

970
00:59:52,160 --> 00:59:54,160
No, no! That's...

971
00:59:54,240 --> 00:59:57,440
No! You... no, no!

972
00:59:57,520 --> 00:59:58,480
No!

973
00:59:58,560 --> 00:59:59,960
Give me my Journal!

974
01:00:03,360 --> 01:00:05,800
Jack! Jack!
What the hell's going on?

975
01:00:05,880 --> 01:00:07,480
Who is that girl, Jack?

976
01:00:07,520 --> 01:00:10,040
- Whoa! Jeez!
- Sorry!

977
01:00:10,120 --> 01:00:12,480
Jeez, I'm sorry.
Sorry.

978
01:00:20,320 --> 01:00:22,720
Why are these people
chasing us, you asshole?

979
01:00:22,760 --> 01:00:23,720
I'll tell you later.

980
01:00:25,440 --> 01:00:26,720
Jeez!

981
01:00:28,160 --> 01:00:29,440
Aw, Jack!

982
01:00:39,360 --> 01:00:40,960
Give me the Journal, Jack.

983
01:00:41,920 --> 01:00:43,920
- That's what she wants?
- You gave your Journal to her?

984
01:00:44,000 --> 01:00:44,920
Give it to her!
Give it to her!

985
01:00:44,960 --> 01:00:46,280
- Give it to her!
- Wait a second!

986
01:01:18,920 --> 01:01:20,160
Fuck it, abort.

987
01:01:30,920 --> 01:01:32,000
Yeah?

988
01:01:33,000 --> 01:01:34,560
Okay, I'll take him, but quick!

989
01:01:35,000 --> 01:01:35,840
Hey.

990
01:01:41,160 --> 01:01:43,160
I had my Journal
in my hands today,

991
01:01:43,240 --> 01:01:44,720
and I lost it.

992
01:01:44,800 --> 01:01:46,640
Morty fell,
things went sideways,

993
01:01:46,720 --> 01:01:49,280
confusion ruled, and one of her uncles
picked it up.

994
01:01:50,440 --> 01:01:53,880
Barbi Ling
has my Journal once again.

995
01:01:58,600 --> 01:02:01,960
I headed home knowing
I needed to do something to change my luck,

996
01:02:02,040 --> 01:02:04,440
so I drove to David Lilly's
in Brentwood.

997
01:02:04,520 --> 01:02:08,400
It was time to Jumpstart the beast,
and I knew Just how to do it.

998
01:02:30,520 --> 01:02:31,800
Hello there, neighbor!

999
01:02:31,880 --> 01:02:33,720
Just me, Jack Giamoro,

1000
01:02:33,800 --> 01:02:36,120
your friendly
neighborhood IAA agent.

1001
01:02:36,200 --> 01:02:37,560
What is this?

1002
01:02:37,640 --> 01:02:40,200
David, I'm gonna
make a speech. Okay?

1003
01:02:40,240 --> 01:02:41,560
At the end of this speech,

1004
01:02:41,640 --> 01:02:43,480
